{"title_page": "Always a Witch", "text_new": "{{short description|Colombian Spanish-language drama-fantasy TV series on Netflix}}\n{{use mdy dates|date=January 2020}}\n{{Infobox television\n| show_name          = Always a Witch\n| image              = Always a Witch.jpg\n| caption            = \n| genre              = Fantasy<br>[[Romantic comedy]]\n| creator            = Ana Mar\u00eda Parra\n| based_on           = ''Yo, bruja''<br>by Isidora Chac\u00f3n\n| starring           = [[Angely Gaviria]]<br>Valeria Emiliani<br>[[Ver\u00f3nica Orozco]]<br>Sof\u00eda Bernal Araujo<br>Dylan Fuentes<br>[[Carlos Quintero]]<br>Dub\u00e1n Prado<br>Lenard Vanderaa<br>[[Sebasti\u00e1n Eslava]]<br>Luis Fernando Hoyos<br>Jhon Alex Castillo<br> Oscar Casas\n| composer           = \n| country            = Colombia\n| language           = Spanish<ref name=romper/>\n| num_seasons        = 2\n| num_episodes       = 18\n| list_episodes      = \n| executive_producer = \n| producer           = \n| cinematography     = \n| camera             =\n| editor             = \n| runtime            = \n| company            = \n| distributor        = [[Netflix]]\n| picture_format     =\n| audio              = \n| first_aired        = January 1, 2019\n| last_aired         =\n| website            = https://www.netflix.com/title/80205595\n| website_title      = Official website\n| channel            = [[Netflix]]\n}}\n'''''Always a Witch''''' ({{lang-es|Siempre Bruja}}) is a 2019 Colombian web television series starring [[Angely Gaviria]], Lenard Vanderaa and Carlos Quintero. The plot revolves around Carmen Eguiluz (Angely Gaviria), a witch and slave from 1646, and is set both in the 17th-century and present-day [[Cartagena, Colombia]].<ref name=dailydot/>\n\nIt was ordered direct-to-series, and the first full season premiered on Netflix streaming on January 1, 2019. It was renewed by Netflix for a second season, which aired worldwide on February 28, 2020.<ref name=whatson/> The show is dubbed in English for US audiences.<ref name=romper/>\n\n==Premise==\nIn ''Always a Witch'', Carmen Eguiluz (Angely Gaviria) is accused of witchcraft and is set to burn at the stake according to the way of the Inquisition in the 1646 colonial Colombia. While imprisoned and waiting for her execution, Carmen makes a deal with the wizard Aldemar, which makes her able to time-travel to 2019 in exchange for a favor. She won't be able to use magic there though, since it would make Lucien, a powerful but evil wizard, aware of her presence.<ref name=decider/><ref name=femestella/><ref name=mediaversityreviews/>\n\n==Reception==\nThe series has received mixed reviews from critics.  While some praised the show for having a strong black female lead character, others have criticized the slave/slave master romance, and the lead character's willingness to return to the 1600s, thus returning to being a slave, just to be with her white slave master boyfriend.<ref name=whatson/><ref name=medium/><ref name=remezcla/><ref name=refinery29/><ref name=vox/>\n\n==Cast==\n===Main===\n* [[Angely Gaviria]] as Carmen Eguiluz, a powerful witch from the 1640s who is propelled forward in time to 2019.\n* Lenard Vanderaa as Cristobal De Aranoa, Carmen's lover in 1646. \n* Carlos Quintero as Le\u00f3n, Mayte's boyfriend and one of Carmen's friends in 2019.  \n* [[Sebasti\u00e1n Eslava]] as Esteban, Carmen's, Le\u00f3n's, Alicia's, Mayte's and Daniel's professor in 2019. \n* Cristina Warner as Isabel de Aranoa, Cristobal's mother in 1646. \n* Sofia Bernal Araujo as Alicia, Carmen's friend in 2019. \n* [[Valeria Henr\u00edquez]] as Mayte, Le\u00f3n's girlfriend and one of Carmen's friends in 2019. \n* Dylan Fuentes as Johnny Ki, Carmen's best friend and confidante in 2019. \n* [[Ver\u00f3nica Orozco]] as Ninib\u00e9, a biology professor and Aldemar's proteg\u00e9 in 2019. (Season 1)\n* Luis Fernando Hoyos as Aldemar the Immortal, a powerful wizard held captive in 1646. (Season 1)\n* Oscar Casas as Kobo, a pirate from the late 17th century who finds himself in 2020. (Season 2)\n\n===Recurring===\n* Juan Manuel Mendoza as Detective Pablo Corcel, the policeman in charge of the Fire Killer case in 2019. (Season 1) \n* John Alex Castillo as Braulio, Carmen's uncle in 1646. (Season 1)\n* Constanza Duque as Adelaida, Johnny Ki's grandmother and the owner of the hostel where he and Carmen live in 2019. (Season 1) \n* Mayra Luna as Hilda, a slave and Carmen's best friend in 1646.\n* Edu Mart\u00edn as Fernando De Aranoa, Cristobal's father in 1646. (Season 1)\n* Norma Nivia as Ximena Gamez, Ninibe's disciple and another professor in 2019. (Season 1) \n* Dub\u00e1n Andr\u00e9s Prado as Daniel, one of Carmen's friends in 2019.\n\n===Guest===\n* Felix Mercado as Rogelio\n* Indhira Serrano as Dr. Luisa\n\n==Episodes==\n{{Series overview\n| allreleased = y\n| released    = y\n| color1      = #FED403\n| link1       = #Season 1 (2019)\n| episodes1   = 10\n| start1      = {{Start date|2019|2|19|df=y}}\n\n| color2      = #0244A4\n| link2       = #Season 2 (2020)\n| episodes2   = 8\n| start2      = {{Start date|2020|2|28|df=y}}\n}}\n===Season 1 (2019)=== \n{{Episode table |background=#FED403 |overall=5 |season=5 |title=22 |director=12 |writer=25 |airdate= |episodes=\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber   = 1\n| EpisodeNumber2  = 1\n| Title           = A Leap in Time\n| DirectedBy      = Liliana Bocanegra\n| WrittenBy       = Ana Maria Parra\n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2019|2|1}}\n| ShortSummary    = In Cartagena, 1646, Carmen Eguiluz is accused of witchcraft during the Spanish Inquisition and sentenced to burn at the stake. However, prior to burning, she travels through time to the year 2019 where she is taken to a hospital. The hospital staff are concerned by the burns on her feat and contact the police. Detective Corcel arrives believing Carmen may be a victim of the Fire Killer, who has murdered several young women in Cartagena. She escapes before being questioned, and begins searching for someone named Ninibe. She evades the police by hiding in the former De Aranoa home, now a hostel, and meets Johnny Ki, the owner's grandson. She then goes to the University and finds Ninibe, a biology professor, and gives her a green stone. Ninibe promises to return Carmen to the past, but before she can, she is attacked by a shadowy being and vanishes. Carmen is captured by the police. \n\nIn a flashback to 1646, Carmen is sold on the slave market. She is purchased by the family of Cristobal De Aranoa and the two fall in love. However, they are caught by Cristobal's mother, Isabel, who accuses Carmen of bewitching her son. Cristobal tries to defend her from the mob and is shot by his father. Carmen is thrown in prison where she meets a wizard, Aldemar the Immortal. He offers her a deal, he will save Cristobal if Carmen travels to the future to find a woman named Ninibe and break Aldemar's curse. He warns her that if she uses magic, she will summon the evil wizard Lucien.  \n| LineColor       = FED403\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber   = 2\n| EpisodeNumber2  = 2\n| Title           = A University Witch\n| DirectedBy      = Liliana Bocanegra\n| WrittenBy       = Ana Maria Parra \n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2019|2|1}}\n| ShortSummary    = Carmen is interrogated by Corcel, and is eventually released. A university student, Alicia, is also questioned as she was seen arguing with Ninibe shortly before the latter's disappearance. At the hostel, Johnny Ki sees Carmen levitating in her sleep and takes a video. Carmen follows Alicia to the University, believing her to be the disciple mentioned by Ninibe. She joins the class, now taught by Esteban. She joins Alicia and Daniel at a welcome party for the biology students and discovers she can see memories by touching people's skin. She follows Alicia to Ninibe's home where Alicia is trying to download files from Ninibe's computer. However, they are interrupted by another woman and Carmen helps Alicia escape. Alicia reveals that she is being blackmailed by her ex-boyfriend, Angel, with an incriminating video and that she had gone to Ninibe for help. Carmen gives Alicia a potion to make her ex-boyfriend forget their relationship. However, the potion fails and Angel sends the video to Alicia's close friends. Carmen meanwhile has a vision of Ninibe in a forest, and discovers a burned skeleton. She writes a letter to Cristobal and tucks it in the gap above the window where they used to leave each other messages. Johnny Ki confronts Carmen about being a witch and says he needs her help. \n| LineColor       = FED403\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber   = 3\n| EpisodeNumber2  = 3\n| Title           = Ouija \n| DirectedBy      = Louis Milito\n| WrittenBy       = Jason Ning & Jenn Kao\n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2019|2|1}}\n| ShortSummary    = \n| LineColor       = FED403\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber   = 4\n| EpisodeNumber2  = 4\n| Title           = Stolen Shadow, Witch Forgotten \n| DirectedBy      = [[Matt Earl Beesley]]\n| WrittenBy       = [[Ildy Modrovich]]\n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2019|2|1}}\n| ShortSummary    = \n| LineColor       = FED403\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber   = 5\n| EpisodeNumber2  = 5\n| Title           = The Festival of Candela \n| DirectedBy      = [[Tim Matheson]]\n| WrittenBy       = [[Sheri Elwood]]\n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2019|2|1}}\n| ShortSummary    = \n| LineColor       = FED403\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber   = 6\n| EpisodeNumber2  = 6\n| Title           = The Ritual of Forgetting \n| DirectedBy      = Mateo Stivelberg\n| WrittenBy       = Jason Ning\n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2019|2|1}}\n| ShortSummary    = \n| LineColor       = FED403\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber   = 7\n| EpisodeNumber2  = 7\n| Title           = Lucien\n| DirectedBy      = Mateo Stivelberg\n| WrittenBy       = Alex Katsnelson\n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2019|2|1}}\n| ShortSummary    = \n| LineColor       = FED403\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber   = 8\n| EpisodeNumber2  = 8\n| Title           = 1646\n| DirectedBy      = Mateo Stivelberg\n| WrittenBy       = Jenn Kao\n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2019|2|1}}\n| ShortSummary    = \n| LineColor       = FED403\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber   = 9\n| EpisodeNumber2  = 9\n| Title           = The Time Portal \n| DirectedBy      = Mateo Stivelberg\n| WrittenBy       = [[Chris Rafferty]]\n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2019|2|1}}\n| ShortSummary    = \n| LineColor       = FED403\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber   = 10\n| EpisodeNumber2  = 10\n| Title           = The Final Trip \n| DirectedBy      = Mateo Stivelberg\n| WrittenBy       = Alex Katsnelson & [[Mike Costa]]\n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2019|2|1}}\n| ShortSummary    = Carmen and her friends decide they must stop Aldemar. Meanwhile, Aldemar returns to the Time Portal with Ninibe so he might travel and find other great witches and wizards and learn their secrets, however the green stone is gone and Ninibe begins to suspect she is being used. Aldemar attacks and bewitches Daniel who tells Carmen that Esteban escaped and she will never see him again. Mayte and Alicia infiltrate Ninibe's Women's Circle in hopes of finding clues to Aldemar's or Esteban's whereabouts. There, Alicia witnesses Ninibe threaten Sandra into returning the ''Book of Shadows''. Ninibe then bewitches Mayte and Alicia. Carmen uses the Ouija board to contact Esteban but finds Aldemar instead. Aldemar claims that he will set Esteban free if Carmen delivers the green stone. Carmen concocts a plan to capture Aldemar unaware that several of her friends are now his unwilling agents. Aldemar confronts Sandra about the ''Book of Shadows'', but when asked for more time he turns her to ash to Ninibe's horror. Meanwhile, Leon reveals the truth of Carmen's origins and Aldemar to Detective Corcel, and Aldemar meets with Carmen to retrieve the stone. There, Aldemar reveals that Esteban escaped by joining him and attacks Carmen when she refuses to do the same. However, when Aldemar attempts to burn her alive, Esteban turns against him and receives a mortal wound. Johnny Ki steals Aldemar's shadow, freeing Daniel, Alicia and Mayte from his spell, and he dissolves into ash. Carmen, whose powers have returned, heals Esteban, and Corcel, who witnessed the entire showdown, leaves to take Ninibe into custody. Ninibe, however, proves she is not the Fire Killer with a video of Aldemar killing Sandra and Corcel is forced to let her go. Carmen uses her powers to allow Johnny Ki to say goodbye to his parents, gently rebuffs Esteban, and prepares to return to the past. Before she can, Cristobal arrives through the Portal and Carmen realizes that Johnny Ki has gone back in time to try and save his parents, mistakenly going to the 17th century. It is revealed that Johnny Ki has been captured by pirates, who take him aboard a ship to an unknown location. \n| LineColor       = FED403\n}}\n}}\n\n===Season 2 (2020)===\n{{Episode table |background=#0244A4 |overall= |season=|title= |director= |writer= |airdate= |released=y |episodes=\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber   = 11\n |EpisodeNumber2  = 1\n |Title           = Someone Like Me\n |DirectedBy      =  \n |WrittenBy       = \n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2020|2|28}}\n |ShortSummary    = Carmen and Alicia find Johnny Ki in the 17th century, but he begs them for more time in the past. The group celebrates his impending return at their favorite bar, where Carmen's palm reading skills attract the attention of another group of students: Amanda, Miguel, and Tomas. Esteban warns Carmen to be careful about advertising her skills, but she admits that she wants to find another lineage witch to open a secret chapter of the ''Book of Shadows''. When Leon complains of being overworked, Carmen makes him a potion to help, but Daniel steals it and starts distributing it.\n |LineColor       = 0244A4\n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber   = 12\n |EpisodeNumber2  = 2\n |Title           = Leeches\n |DirectedBy      = \n |WrittenBy       = \n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2020|2|28}}\n |ShortSummary    = \n |LineColor       = 0244A4\n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber   = 13\n |EpisodeNumber2  = 3\n |Title           = Antares\n |DirectedBy      = \n |WrittenBy       = \n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2020|2|28}}\n |ShortSummary    = \n |LineColor       = 0244A4\n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber   = 14\n |EpisodeNumber2  = 4\n |Title           = Mr. Hyde\n |DirectedBy      = \n |WrittenBy       = \n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2020|2|28}}\n |ShortSummary    = \n |LineColor       = 0244A4\n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber   = 15\n |EpisodeNumber2  = 5\n |Title           = A Crack in Time\n |DirectedBy      = \n |WrittenBy       = \n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2020|2|28}}\n |ShortSummary    = \n |LineColor       = 0244A4\n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber   = 16\n |EpisodeNumber2  = 6\n |Title           = From Student to Master \n |DirectedBy      = \n |WrittenBy       = \n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2020|2|28}}\n |ShortSummary    = \n |LineColor       = 0244A4\n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber   = 17\n |EpisodeNumber2  = 7\n |Title           = One Last Wish\n |DirectedBy      = \n |WrittenBy       = \n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2020|2|28}}\n |ShortSummary    = \n |LineColor       = 0244A4\n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber   = 18\n |EpisodeNumber2  = 8\n |Title           = Impossible\n |DirectedBy      = \n |WrittenBy       = \n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2020|2|28}}\n |ShortSummary    = \n |LineColor       = 0244A4\n}}\n}}\nWho are the names of the pirates?\n\n==Release==\nThe first full season consisting of 10 episodes premiered on Netflix streaming on January 1, 2019.<ref name=netflix/> It was renewed by Netflix for a second season, which started airing worldwide on February 28, 2020.<ref name=whatson/>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|refs=\n<ref name=romper>{{cite web\n| fir