dercover for the French Secret Service as a female secretary.\n |LineColor       = \n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber  = 18\n |Title           = {{lang|fr|Le miroir se brisa}}\n |Aux1            = [[The Mirror Crack'd from Side to Side]]\n |DirectedBy      = Rodolphe Tissot\n |OriginalAirDate = 2017\n |ShortSummary    = Investigating a murder becomes complicated for Laurence as he mourns his own loss.\n |LineColor       = \n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber  = 19\n |Title           = {{lang|fr|Crimes haute couture}}\n |Aux1            = [[Third Girl]]\n |DirectedBy      = [[Nicolas Picard-Dreyfuss]]\n |OriginalAirDate = 2017\n |ShortSummary    = After a young fashionista accuses herself of murder, Laurence has to find the real killer.\n |LineColor       = \n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber  = 20\n |Title           = {{lang|fr|Crime de No\u00ebl}}\n |Aux1            = not adapted\n |DirectedBy      = Rodolphe Tissot\n |OriginalAirDate = 2017\n |ShortSummary    = Two orphans witness the murder of a Santa Claus at an outdoor Christmas market; an original story.\n |LineColor       = \n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber  = 21\n |Title           = {{lang|fr|Drame en trois actes}}\n |Aux1            = [[Three Act Tragedy]]\n |DirectedBy      = Nicolas Picard-Dreyfuss\n |OriginalAirDate = 2018\n |ShortSummary    = Murder befalls Alice's acting class, which features a guest teacher who looks exactly like Laurence.\n |LineColor       = \n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber  = 22\n |Title           = {{lang|fr|Meurtres en solde}}\n |Aux1            = [[Hercule Poirot's Christmas]]\n |DirectedBy      = [[Didier Bivel]]\n |OriginalAirDate = 2018\n |ShortSummary    = Avril is attacked and struggles with amnesia while working on an article. The bodies of a man and a woman are found at a car crash and the deaths look suspicious. (This adaptation has no Christmas theme.)\n |LineColor       = \n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber  = 23\n |Title           = {{lang|fr|M\u00e9lodie Mortelle}}\n |Aux1            = [[The Sittaford Mystery]]\n |DirectedBy      = [[Christophe Campos]]\n |OriginalAirDate = 2018\n |ShortSummary    = &nbsp;\n |LineColor       = \n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber  = 24\n |Title           = {{lang|fr|Ding Dingue Dong}}\n |Aux1            = [[Evil Under the Sun]]\n |DirectedBy      = Christophe Campos\n |OriginalAirDate = 2019\n |ShortSummary    = &nbsp;\n |LineColor       = \n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber  = 25\n |Title           = {{lang|fr|L'Heure Zero}}\n |Aux1            = [[Towards Zero]]\n |DirectedBy      = Nicolas Picard-Dreyfuss\n |OriginalAirDate = 2019\n |ShortSummary    = &nbsp;\n |LineColor       = \n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber  = 26\n |Title           = {{lang|fr|Rendez-vous avec la Mort}}\n |Aux1            = [[Appointment with Death]]\n |DirectedBy      = Nicolas Picard-Dreyfuss\n |OriginalAirDate = 2019\n |ShortSummary    = &nbsp;\n |LineColor       = \n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber  = 27\n |Title           = {{lang|fr|Un Cadavre au Petit D\u00e9jeuner}}\n |Aux1            = not adapted\n |DirectedBy      = Nicolas Picard-Dreyfuss\n |OriginalAirDate = 2019/2020\n |ShortSummary    = Original musical-comedy episode;<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.sbs.com.au/ondemand/video/1676468291833/agatha-christies-criminal-games-a-body-with-breakfast|title=Agatha Christie's Criminal Games: A Body with Breakfast|last=|first=|date=|website=SBS On Demand|language=en|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-04-15}}</ref> first aired in Italy in 2019, Australia in 2020, and in France expected late 2020)<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.mondofox.it/guida-tv/foxcrime/2019-10-31/|title=GUIDA TV di FoxCrime di gioved\u00ec 31 ottobre 2019|last=|first=|date=31 October 2019|website=MondoFox|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=14 April 2020}}</ref><ref>{{Citation|title=\"Les petits meurtres d'Agatha Christie\" Un cadavre au petit d\u00e9jeuner (TV Episode 2019) - IMDb|url=http://www.imdb.com/title/tt10269126/releaseinfo|access-date=2020-04-14}}</ref><ref name=\"telestar\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.telestar.fr/actu-tv/exclu-telestar-les-petits-meurtres-d-agatha-christie-ce-n-est-pas-fini-467484|title=EXCLU TELESTAR. Les Petits meurtres d'Agatha Christie ce n'est... - T\u00e9l\u00e9 Star|last=Telestar.fr|date=2019-10-28|website=www.telestar.fr|language=fr|access-date=2020-04-14}}</ref>\n |LineColor       = \n}}\n}}\n\n== Series Three: 1970s France (announced 2019) ==\nA third series, with a new cast and set in France in the 1970s, was announced in 2019. The first episode is expected to be released in late 2020.<ref name=\"telestar\" /><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.programme.tv/news/series/208867-emotion-dans-greys-anatomy-la-nouvelle-saison-des-petits-meurtres-dagatha-christie-et-les-abdos-de-loup-denis-elion-les-tournages-de-la-semaine-photos/|title=Emotion dans Grey\u2019s Anatomy, la nouvelle saison des Petits Meurtres d\u2019Agatha Christie et les abdos de Loup-Denis Elion\u2026 Les tournages de la semaine (PHOTOS) - series - T\u00e9l\u00e9 2 semaines|website=www.programme.tv/news|access-date=2020-04-14}}</ref>\n\n==See also==\n* [[List of French television series]]\n\n==Trivia==\n* In the second season of the French TV series \"{{lang|fr|Les Petits Meurtres d'Agatha Christie}}\", Commissaire Swan Laurence drives a [[Facel Vega]] Facellia FA red Bordeaux coupe.<ref>{{cite web|title=V\u00e9hicule du film \"les petits meurtres d'Agatha Christie\"|periodical=|publisher=|url=https://www.lesanciennes.com/annonce/A312537-ventes-auto-facel-vega-facellia-fa-coupe-2-2-1960.html?ftype=&fcat=&search=FACEL%20VEGA|url-status=|format=|access-date=2020-04-09|archive-url=|archive-date=|last=|date=2020-03-08|year=|language=|pages=|quote=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Facel Vega \u00e1 la T\u00e9l\u00e9vision|periodical=|publisher=|url=http://www.facel-vega.asso.fr/tv/tv.html|url-status=|format=|access-date=2020-04-09|archive-url=|archive-date=|last=|date=2013-03-29|year=|language=|pages=|quote=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=RR Forums Australia|periodical=|publisher=|url=http://au.rrforums.net/forum/messages/16947/22770.html?1479246125|url-status=|format=|access-date=2020-04-09|archive-url=|archive-date=|last=|date=2016-11-15|year=|language=|pages=|quote=}}</ref>\n\n== 2006 mini-series ==\nA distinct four-part mini-series, \"{{lang|fr|Petits Meurtres en Famille}}\", adapted from ''[[Hercule Poirot's Christmas]]'', was released in 2006. Although Larosi\u00e8re and Lampion are the main characters (played by the same actors), this mini-series is not a prequel or sequel to the later series.\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{IMDb title|id=1349600|title=Les Petits Meurtres d'Agatha Christie}}\n\n{{Television needs character section}}{{Television needs production section}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Petits Meurtres d'Agatha Christie}}\n[[Category:2009 French television series debuts]]\n[[Category:2000s French television series]]\n[[Category:2010s French television series]]\n[[Category:French crime television series]]\n[[Category:French-language television programs]]\n[[Category:Television programmes based on works by Agatha Christie]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|French TV detective series 2006, 2009\u20132019}}\n{{EngvarB|date=April 2020}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2020}}\n{{Infobox television\n| show_name                = {{lang|fr|Les Petits Meurtres d'Agatha Christie}}\n| image                    = Les Petits Meurtres d'Agatha Christie.png\n| genre                    = Detective mystery\n| creator                  = Anne Giafferi <br/> [[Murielle Magellan]]\n| writer                   = \n| director                 = \n| starring                 = ''Series One'':<br/>\n[[Antoine Dul\u00e9ry]]<br/>\n[[Marius Colucci]]<br/>\n''Series Two'':<br/>\n[[Samuel Labarthe]]<br/>\n[[Blandine Bellavoir]]<br/>\n[[\u00c9lodie Frenck]]<br/>\n| composer                 = \n| country                  = France\n| location                 = France\n| language                 = French\n| num_series               = 2\n| num_episodes             = 11 {{!}} 27\n| list_episodes            = \n| executive_producer       = \n| company                  = Escazai Films\n| distributor              = FranceTv, RLJ-Acorn (DVD), MHZ (USTV) (DVD)\n| camera                   = \n| runtime                  = 100 minutes\n| network                  = [[France 2]]\n| picture_format           = [[480i]] ([[Standard-definition television|SDTV]]) <br> [[720p]] ([[High-definition television|HDTV]])\n| first_aired              = 9 January 2009\n| last_aired               = present<ref name=\"telestar\" />\n| website                  = http://www.france2.fr/emissions/les-petits-meurtres-d-agatha-christie\n| show_name_2              = The Little Murders of Agatha Christie; Agatha Christie's Criminal Games\n| based_on                 = [[Agatha Christie]]'s detective fiction\n| preceded_by              = {{lang|fr|Petits Meurtres en Famille}} 2006 (4-part mini-series)\n}}\n'''{{lang|fr|Les Petits Meurtres d'Agatha Christie}}''' (English title: \"'''''The Little Murders of Agatha Christie'''''\") is a French-language television program consisting of two series loosely based on [[Agatha Christie|Agatha Christie's]] works of detective fiction. First broadcast on [[France 2]] on 9 January [[2009 in television|2009]],<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.agathachristie.com/film-and-tv/les-petits-meurtres-dagatha-christie|title=Les Petits Meurtres d'Agatha Christie|last=|first=|date=2020|website=The Home of Agatha Christie|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=13 April 2020}}</ref> Series One takes place in 1930s France with {{lang|fr|Commissaire}} (approximately [[Chief inspector#United%20Kingdom|DCI]]) Larosi\u00e8re ([[Antoine Dul\u00e9ry]]) and {{Lang|fr|Inspecteur}} Lampion ([[Marius Colucci]]). Series Two is set in mid-1950s through 1960s France with Commissaire Laurence ([[Samuel Labarthe]]),<ref> {{Cite web|url=https://www.agathachristie.com/film-and-tv/les-petits-meurtres-dagatha-christie/meet-the-characters/samuel-labarthe|title=Samuel Labarthe|last=|first=|date=|website=The Home of Agatha Christie|language=en-US|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-04-13}} </ref> his secretary Marl\u00e8ne Leroy ([[\u00c9lodie Frenck]]), and newspaper reporter Alice Avril ([[Blandine Bellavoir]]). In English-speaking countries, the second series is titled \"Agatha Christie's Criminal Games\" and has streamed on [[MHz Choice]] in the United States and [[Special Broadcasting Service|SBS]] in Australia.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://watch.mhzchoice.com/agatha-christie-s-criminal-games|title=Agatha Christie's Criminal Games|website=MHz Choice|language=en|access-date=2020-04-13}}</ref><ref> {{Cite web|url=https://www.sbs.com.au/ondemand/program/agatha-christies-criminal-games|title=Agatha Christie's Criminal Games|last=|first=|date=|website=SBS On Demand|language=en|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-04-13}}</ref> The thirty-eight episodes to the end of Series Two include adaptations of thirty-six of Christie's works.\n\nA third series, with a new cast and set in 1970s France, was announced in 2019.<ref name=\"telestar\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.telestar.fr/actu-tv/exclu-telestar-les-petits-meurtres-d-agatha-christie-ce-n-est-pas-fini-467484|title=EXCLU TELESTAR. Les Petits meurtres d'Agatha Christie ce n'est... - T\u00e9l\u00e9 Star|last=Telestar.fr|date=2019-10-28|website=www.telestar.fr|language=fr|access-date=2020-04-14}}</ref>\n\n==Cast==\n{| class=\"wikitable mw-collapsible mw-collapsed center\" style=\"font-size: 86%; width:60%; left:0 auto; text-align:center;\"\n|+ align=\"center\" colspan=\"4\" | <big>{{nowrap|Cast of Series One and Series Two}}</big>\n|- style=\"background-color: #CCCCFF\" \n| '''Casting'''|| '''Character''' || '''Episodes''' || scope=\"col\" style=\"width: 80px;\" | '''Year'''\n